WEBVTT

00:05.105 --> 00:06.073 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:06.106 --> 00:07.074 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.107 --> 00:08.775 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And I'm Gwen Ifill.

00:08.809 --> 00:11.845 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: On the "NewsHour"
tonight:
President Obama weighs in on the
presidential

00:11.879 --> 00:17.651 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
campaign, as Donald Trump's feud
with the
Khan family has more Republicans
distancing

00:17.684 --> 00:20.087 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
themselves from their party
nominee.

00:20.120 --> 00:24.625 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Also ahead this
Tuesday: controlling
Zika in the United States.

00:24.658 --> 00:31.431 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The CDC issues an unprecedented
warning urging
pregnant women to stay away from
a Miami neighborhood

00:31.465 --> 00:33.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
where the virus is spreading.

00:33.233 --> 00:38.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And debating the
math myth
-- why one college professor
says advanced

00:38.805 --> 00:41.541 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
math classes are not only
unnecessary, but
harmful.

00:41.575 --> 00:45.145 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ANDREW HACKER, Professor
Emeritus, Queens
College: We immediately plunge
people into

00:45.178 --> 00:47.781 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
geometry and algebra.

00:47.814 --> 00:52.920 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, as a result, Americans are
really quite
illiterate in terms of numbers.

00:52.953 --> 01:00.294 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: All that and more on
tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:00.327 --> 01:02.996 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:03.030 --> 01:12.572 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A presidential
broadside today
aimed at Donald Trump.

01:12.606 --> 01:17.077 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Obama took on the man
who is running
to succeed him in his strongest
terms yet.

01:17.110 --> 01:20.914 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
I think the Republican nominee
is unfit to

01:20.948 --> 01:22.182 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
serve as president.

01:22.215 --> 01:27.187 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I said so last week, and he
keeps on proving
it.

01:27.220 --> 01:32.292 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The rebuke came
at a news conference
with the visiting prime minister
of Singapore.

01:32.326 --> 01:37.664 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president drew a sharp
distinction between
Donald Trump and the Republican
nominees he

01:37.698 --> 01:40.467 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
had faced, John McCain and Mitt
Romney.

01:40.500 --> 01:45.205 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: I never thought
that they couldn't
do the job.

01:45.238 --> 01:53.547 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And had they won, I would have
been disappointed,
but I would have said to all
Americans, they

01:53.580 --> 02:00.754 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are -- this is our president and
I know they
are going to abide by certain
norms and rules

02:00.787 --> 02:05.659 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and common sense, will observe
basic decency.

02:05.692 --> 02:12.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All of this
followed Trump's
repeated criticisms of Khizr and
Ghazala Khan,

02:12.699 --> 02:17.037 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
parents of a U.S. army officer
who died in
Iraq.

02:17.070 --> 02:21.174 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Republican leaders condemned the
remarks,
but Mr. Obama said that's not
enough.

02:21.208 --> 02:28.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: This is daily and
weekly where
they are distancing themselves
from statements

02:28.782 --> 02:30.550 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
he's making.

02:30.584 --> 02:35.555 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There has to be a point at which
you say,
this is not somebody I can
support for president

02:35.589 --> 02:37.357 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of the United States.

02:37.391 --> 02:42.162 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: One New York
Republican congressman,
Richard Hanna, did just that
today.

02:42.195 --> 02:47.634 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In a newspaper opinion
columnist, he wrote:
"Mr. Trump has attacked the
parents of a slain

02:47.667 --> 02:49.102 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
U.S. soldier.

02:49.136 --> 02:51.004 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Where do we draw the line?

02:51.038 --> 02:56.810 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
While I disagree with her on
many issues,
I will vote for Hillary
Clinton."

02:56.843 --> 03:01.915 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Trump was speaking in Northern
Virginia as
the president held his news
conference, and

03:01.948 --> 03:06.319 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he made no mention of the Obama
criticism
or the Khans.

03:06.353 --> 03:08.188 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But it was in the air just the
same.

03:08.221 --> 03:15.128 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), Presidential
Candidate:
A man came up to me and he
handed me his Purple

03:15.162 --> 03:16.863 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Heart.

03:16.897 --> 03:21.668 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The Purple Heart,
given to
those wounded or killed in
action, came from

03:21.701 --> 03:23.170 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a retired lieutenant colonel.

03:23.203 --> 03:26.540 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: I always wanted to
get the Purple
Heart.

03:26.573 --> 03:28.308 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This was much easier.

03:28.341 --> 03:33.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Later, Trump did
answer the
president in a statement,
charging he and

03:33.280 --> 03:39.152 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
his former secretary of state
betrayed American
security and American workers.

03:39.186 --> 03:45.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Trump declared -- quote --
"Hillary Clinton
has proven herself unfit to
serve in any government

03:45.826 --> 03:47.227 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
office."

03:47.260 --> 03:51.565 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Trump supporters at the rally
appeared unfazed
by the latest blowup.

03:51.598 --> 03:53.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: The coverage is just
insane.

03:53.733 --> 03:56.303 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think they make a big deal
about that.

03:56.336 --> 03:59.206 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
First of all, he was speaking
from his heart.

03:59.239 --> 04:01.508 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And he wasn't accusing them or
saying anything.

04:01.541 --> 04:05.178 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Trump moves on to
campaign
in Florida tomorrow.

04:05.212 --> 04:08.582 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Clinton will be in Colorado.

04:08.615 --> 04:13.320 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also today, Donald Trump told
The Washington
Post he is not ready to endorse
Republican

04:13.353 --> 04:16.089 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
House Speaker Paul Ryan for
reelection.

04:16.123 --> 04:22.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He also said he won't support
Republican Senators
John McCain and Kelly Ayotte for
new terms.

04:22.295 --> 04:27.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: In the day's other
news: The president
also made a renewed pitch for
the Trans-Pacific

04:27.434 --> 04:31.671 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Partnership, the trade deal he's
pushing in
the face of growing opposition.

04:31.705 --> 04:35.976 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Both presidential candidates
oppose it, but
Mr. Obama warned against trying
to pull back

04:36.009 --> 04:38.211 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
on trade, and away from
globalization.

04:38.245 --> 04:43.650 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: To try to pull up
a drawbridge
on trade would only hurt us and
hurt our workers.

04:43.683 --> 04:48.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, the answer is to make sure
that globalization
and trade is working for us, not
against us.

04:48.622 --> 04:52.292 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And TPP is designed to do
precisely that.

04:52.325 --> 04:56.796 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The president also
played down
Russia's possible role in
hacking the Democratic

04:56.830 --> 04:58.765 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
National Committee's e-mails.

04:58.798 --> 05:02.402 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He said it only adds to an
already long list
of differences.

05:02.435 --> 05:06.840 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: There's more
fallout from those
Democratic Party e-mails that
showed staffers

05:06.873 --> 05:10.844 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
favoring Hillary Clinton and
disparaging Bernie
Sanders.

05:10.877 --> 05:16.316 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Associated Press reports the
DNC's chief
executive has resigned, and two
other staffers

05:16.349 --> 05:17.784 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
also quit today.

05:17.817 --> 05:22.155 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Party chair, Congresswoman
Debbie Wasserman
Schultz, resigned last week.

05:22.189 --> 05:28.361 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: In Syria, rebels
accused government
forces of a new chemical weapons
attack today.

05:28.395 --> 05:34.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They say a helicopter dropped
barrels of toxic
gas in Idlib province, near
where a Russian

05:34.301 --> 05:38.138 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
helicopter was shot down Monday;
33 people
were affected.

05:38.171 --> 05:43.143 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Video posted on social media
showed victims
being treated with oxygen, but
it's unclear

05:43.176 --> 05:45.045 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
what kind of gas was used.

05:45.078 --> 05:49.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Thousands of
mourners in Normandy,
France, attended a funeral mass
today for

05:49.683 --> 05:51.518 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a murdered Catholic priest.

05:51.551 --> 05:56.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Father Jacques Hamel had his
throat cut by
Islamic State militants last
week.

05:56.756 --> 06:03.163 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, an archbishop led a
solemn public ceremony
inside the Rouen Cathedral to
pay tribute

06:03.196 --> 06:04.164 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to the cleric.

06:04.197 --> 06:06.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He was later buried in a private
service.

06:06.299 --> 06:12.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The death toll has
climbed past
90 across India, after a week of
monsoon flooding.

06:12.672 --> 06:15.475 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A million other people have been
forced to
flee.

06:15.508 --> 06:20.146 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The flooding has caused heavy
damage across
three states in the northern and
eastern parts

06:20.180 --> 06:21.248 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of the country.

06:21.281 --> 06:24.217 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It follows two straight years of
widespread
drought.

06:24.251 --> 06:28.955 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Back in the U.S.,
New York
City Police Commissioner Bill
Bratton is stepping

06:28.989 --> 06:30.757 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
down.

06:30.790 --> 06:35.962 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He led the nation's largest
force in the 1990s,
and returned to the position in
2014.

06:35.996 --> 06:41.801 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He said today he's leaving at a
time of extreme
tensions between police and
minorities, but

06:41.835 --> 06:43.870 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
said he's confident in the
department's future.

06:43.903 --> 06:46.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRATTON, New York City
Police Commissioner:
The mistrust of the criminal
justice system,

06:46.940 --> 06:50.877 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
particularly by our minority
communities,
the immigration issues that are
so paramount

06:50.910 --> 07:00.287 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
at the moment, the anger
directed at our Muslim
community, we, I believe, in New
York City

07:00.320 --> 07:03.990 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at this time are better prepared
than anyplace
else in America.

07:04.024 --> 07:09.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Bratton has been
hailed for
cutting crime, but criticized
over incidents

07:09.296 --> 07:11.932 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of alleged excessive force by
police.

07:11.965 --> 07:16.603 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
James O'Neill, currently the New
York City
department's top chief, will
take over as

07:16.636 --> 07:18.371 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
commissioner.

07:18.405 --> 07:22.609 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And Wall Street
slipped on lackluster
auto sales and falling oil
prices.

07:22.642 --> 07:26.680 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
lost 90 points
to close at 18313.

07:26.713 --> 07:32.052 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq fell 46 points, and
the S&amp;P 500
gave up 13.

07:32.085 --> 07:37.324 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Still to come on
the "NewsHour":
Florida's fight to contain the
Zika virus;

07:37.357 --> 07:43.363 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the back-story to Donald Trump's
latest comments
on Ukraine; an advocate for
teaching more

07:43.396 --> 07:49.703 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
practical mathematics; and much
more.

07:49.736 --> 08:02.349 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: In Florida, workers
went door
to door today to check for
mosquitoes, and

08:02.382 --> 08:06.853 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to spray in neighborhoods, in
the hope of
clamping down on the Zika virus.

08:06.886 --> 08:12.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Officials say 15 people have
become infected
in Miami's Wynwood neighborhood,
and it's

08:12.425 --> 08:17.597 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
believed these are the first
mosquito-transmitted
cases in the mainland U.S.

08:17.630 --> 08:22.335 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The CDC says the mosquitoes are
proving harder
to eradicate than expected.

08:22.369 --> 08:27.807 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For an on-the-ground look, I'm
joined by Alina
Hudak, the deputy mayor of
Miami-Dade County.

08:27.841 --> 08:29.476 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Thank you for joining us.

08:29.509 --> 08:35.648 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We know now of 15 locally
transmitted case
of Zika infections.

08:35.682 --> 08:39.519 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How many more are likely, and
are you prepared
to handle an increase?

08:39.552 --> 08:42.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALINA HUDAK, Deputy Mayor,
Miami-Dade County,
Florida: Gwen, thank you for the
opportunity

08:42.922 --> 08:46.359 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to speak tonight to you and to
your viewers.

08:46.393 --> 08:50.697 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I would like to clarify first
and foremost
that the confirmed cases in
Miami-Dade County

08:50.730 --> 08:53.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
are 12.

08:53.767 --> 09:00.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I want to reiterate and really
just be very
clear about our mosquito control
program here

09:00.073 --> 09:01.775 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in Miami-Dade County.

09:01.808 --> 09:06.045 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have a very strong and
aggressive program
that we have had in place since
1935.

09:06.079 --> 09:12.185 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have many years of a proven
track record
in managing and controlling
disease.

09:12.218 --> 09:17.290 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We work together with our
Department of Health,
with the Department of
Agriculture.

09:17.323 --> 09:22.595 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have had consultations with
the CDC, and
they are working very closely
with us.

09:22.629 --> 09:28.468 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So we feel very confident that
this can be
contained and it can be
contained to a very

09:28.501 --> 09:31.037 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
small area.

09:31.070 --> 09:35.875 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I want the viewers to understand
that we're
talking about one square mile in
a community

09:35.909 --> 09:42.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that is over 2,000 square miles,
and I think
that's important for context and
for people

09:42.248 --> 09:45.218 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to understand exactly the area
that we're
talking about.

09:45.251 --> 09:51.191 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Why is it confined
so far to this
one area, Wynwood, which
contains an art district

09:51.224 --> 09:54.127 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and attracts people from outside
of the neighborhood?

09:54.160 --> 09:55.628 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Why there?

09:55.662 --> 09:59.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
ALINA HUDAK: You know, I
certainly would be
speculating relative to that.

09:59.799 --> 10:06.706 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have a high international
presence there
and a lot of travel in that
community.

10:06.739 --> 10:12.045 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is unknown exactly how it is
that the transmission
takes place, and obviously there
is a lot

10:12.078 --> 10:16.349 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of focus on the mosquito, but
there are many
unknowns about this disease.

10:16.382 --> 10:22.522 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, you know, quite frankly, we
have been
able to isolate at this point
these particular

10:22.555 --> 10:25.291 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
cases, in consultation with the
Department
of Health.

10:25.325 --> 10:29.496 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Our crews have been there every
single day,
and have been on the ground
since day one.

10:29.529 --> 10:33.132 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The moment that a suspected case
is identified,
our crews are there.

10:33.166 --> 10:34.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They do inspection.

10:34.167 --> 10:35.869 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They do treatment.

10:35.902 --> 10:38.438 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we have, again, a very
aggressive program.

10:38.471 --> 10:43.142 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In addition to that, we have a
very aggressive
outreach program to our
residents, and we're

10:43.176 --> 10:47.080 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
communicating with our residents
regularly
about the part and the role that
they play

10:47.113 --> 10:49.516 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in being our partner with this.

10:49.549 --> 10:50.517 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We want our...

10:50.550 --> 10:51.518 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

10:51.551 --> 10:52.519 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And pardon me.

10:52.552 --> 10:54.387 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What are you asking them to do?

