24:56.095 --> 25:01.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
community; and the troubles
still plaguing
Rio just days before the opening
ceremony.

25:01.734 --> 25:07.373 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first: a report on the
Bakken oil fields
in North Dakota, where
employment and the

25:07.406 --> 25:10.909 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
economy are directly affected by
the price
of oil.

25:10.943 --> 25:16.682 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Oil prices have dropped since
their peak in
2014, and drilling has slowed,
idling rigs

25:16.715 --> 25:21.153 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and sending the once booming
economy into
uncertainty.

25:21.186 --> 25:26.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Inside Energy's Emily Guerin
takes us on a
tour of Oil Bust Alley, a short
stretch of

25:26.492 --> 25:31.230 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
highway where the boom and bust
of the oil
industry plays out.

25:31.263 --> 25:39.071 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EMILY GUERIN: I have spent two
years reporting
on the Bakken oil field in North
Dakota.

25:39.104 --> 25:44.376 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have seen it when it was
booming, back in
2014, and now, when it's
busting.

25:44.410 --> 25:49.381 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's one highway in the oil
field town
of Dickinson, Highway 22, where
you can see

25:49.415 --> 25:51.683 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the entire boom and bust story.

25:51.717 --> 25:57.055 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So we're going on a road trip
through Oil
Bust Alley to see what we can
learn in this

25:57.089 --> 26:03.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
five-mile stretch of road about
how a community
changes when the price of oil
crashes.

26:03.362 --> 26:08.634 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Let's start with the obvious
losers: businesses
directly involved in the
drilling and production

26:08.667 --> 26:09.902 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of oil.

26:09.935 --> 26:13.071 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I'm standing in front a
field of stacked
drilling rigs.

26:13.105 --> 26:15.040 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There's about 27 back there.

26:15.073 --> 26:16.842 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We just counted.

26:16.875 --> 26:19.912 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's actually about the
same amount
that are actively drilling for
oil in North

26:19.945 --> 26:21.313 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Dakota.

26:21.346 --> 26:24.216 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Two years ago, when the price of
oil was high,
there were over 180.

26:24.249 --> 26:30.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's really a sign of how
much things
have slowed down here in the oil
field.

26:30.122 --> 26:37.196 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Every time a drilling rig gets
idled, about
120 people lose their jobs,
people like Kaley

26:37.229 --> 26:42.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Haugen's husband, who worked on
a drilling
rig for over a decade before
being laid off

26:42.267 --> 26:44.069 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
last year.

26:44.102 --> 26:48.707 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Haugen has also seen a huge
impact of the
slowdown on her business, the
Uniform Unit,

26:48.740 --> 26:50.442 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
which is right on Highway 22.

26:50.476 --> 26:53.879 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KALEY HAUGEN, Uniform Unit: We
do uniforms
for a variety of industries.

26:53.912 --> 26:59.451 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We do flame-resistant clothing
for the oil
and gas industry, as well as
electrical.

26:59.485 --> 27:06.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We do scrubs, medical uniforms,
and then we
also have brought in tactical
for EMS management

27:06.492 --> 27:08.293 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
services.

27:08.327 --> 27:11.530 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EMILY GUERIN: The Uniform Unit
just opened
last spring, right as oil prices
were tanking.

27:11.563 --> 27:17.002 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KALEY HAUGEN: If we would've
been operating
two years ago, three years ago,
I would bet

27:17.035 --> 27:19.805 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
90 percent of our business would
have been
oil field.

27:19.838 --> 27:23.308 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now I would say we're pretty
even within the
different fields.

27:23.342 --> 27:29.381 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, I would say 30 percent
oil fields,
30 percent tactical, 30 percent
scrubs, so

27:29.414 --> 27:32.317 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
definitely different than I
thought.

27:32.351 --> 27:36.321 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
EMILY GUERIN: Hotels have also
been hit hard
by the slowdown.

27:36.355 --> 27:41.894 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Over 1,000 new hotel rooms were
built in Dickinson
in the past 12 years.

27:41.927 --> 27:47.299 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Connie Hank and Bill Evans
manage and do maintenance
in three of those hotels just
off Highway

27:47.332 --> 27:49.101 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
22.

27:49.134 --> 27:51.837 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BILL EVANS, Maintenance Worker:
When I got
here in March of '14, there were
no vacancies.

27:51.870 --> 27:56.575 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If somebody checked out, you
already had somebody's
name who was waiting on that
room.

27:56.608 --> 28:02.581 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CONNIE HANK, Manager: You
would've been paying
$80 a night for a single and
almost -- just

28:02.614 --> 28:04.783 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
about $100 for a double.

28:04.816 --> 28:06.585 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That was cheap.

28:06.618 --> 28:09.655 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And now you can get a room for
$32 a night.

28:09.688 --> 28:10.656 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's a big change.

28:10.689 --> 28:12.224 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BILL EVANS: Drastic.

28:12.257 --> 28:17.129 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
EMILY GUERIN: Now their three
hotels are at
less than 30 percent occupancy.

28:17.162 --> 28:20.399 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They end up with a lot of time
on their hands.

28:20.432 --> 28:25.604 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CONNIE HANK: I'm sitting here
waiting, praying
that a car pulls into my parking
lot.

28:25.637 --> 28:28.040 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And that was the truth.

28:28.073 --> 28:30.008 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We look like a bunch of
vultures.

28:30.042 --> 28:33.245 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The minute they walked in the
door, it was
like, hey, thank you for coming
here, you

28:33.278 --> 28:35.047 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
know?

28:35.080 --> 28:38.150 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EMILY GUERIN: Just down the
highway, there
are signs that other parts of
the housing

28:38.183 --> 28:40.419 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
market are also hurting.

28:40.452 --> 28:44.089 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, coming up, there's a man
camp graveyard.

28:44.122 --> 28:51.630 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's just a field full of
trailers that are
just like jumbled together,
almost piled on

28:51.663 --> 28:57.135 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
top of each other, because
people don't have
a need to house these workers
anymore because

28:57.169 --> 29:00.205 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they have laid off so many of
their employees.

29:00.238 --> 29:03.942 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The slowdown in the oil field
hasn't been
uniformly bad.

29:03.976 --> 29:09.247 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Custom cabinet manufacturer TMI
Systems had
25 percent growth last year.

29:09.281 --> 29:16.788 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That means they need a lot of
new workers.

29:16.822 --> 29:21.460 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
General manager Tom Krank says a
few years
ago, the cost of living was high
in Dickinson

29:21.493 --> 29:24.930 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
due to the housing shortage
brought on by
the influx of oil workers.

29:24.963 --> 29:27.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TOM KRANK, General Manager, TMI
Systems: With
the rents where they were at, it
was tough

29:28.000 --> 29:32.838 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to even attract people with
that, because
even though we had good wages,
the rents beyond

29:32.871 --> 29:35.273 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
where they could justify moving
out here to
work for us.

29:35.307 --> 29:38.276 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
EMILY GUERIN: But now there's no
longer a
labor shortage.

29:38.310 --> 29:41.680 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There are far more applicants
than job openings.

29:41.713 --> 29:43.315 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And rental prices are dropping.

29:43.348 --> 29:46.518 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So TMI Systems is having no
trouble hiring.

29:46.551 --> 29:51.790 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TOM KRANK: As time went on, the
oil field
layoffs got deeper and deeper,
and pretty

29:51.823 --> 29:55.127 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
soon we started seeing some of
our former
employees coming back.

29:55.160 --> 29:58.030 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
EMILY GUERIN: Scott Weiand is
one of them.

29:58.063 --> 30:04.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He worked at TMI for 21 years
before leaving
in 2012 load crude oil onto rail
cars.

30:04.169 --> 30:07.706 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SCOTT WEIAND, Installer, TMI
Systems: For
me, I was looking for a
challenge, possibly

30:07.739 --> 30:08.707 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a little higher pay.

30:08.740 --> 30:10.676 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Obviously, that's an attraction
for people.

30:10.709 --> 30:13.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But with the slowdown in the oil
business,
I wanted to look for other
opportunities.

30:13.712 --> 30:17.416 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And one of the first things in
mind for me
was TMI.

30:17.449 --> 30:22.054 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
EMILY GUERIN: The slowdown is
also benefiting
the local government.

30:22.087 --> 30:27.826 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Dickinson City Administrator
Shawn Kessel
says hiring is easier and
expenses are lower,

30:27.859 --> 30:31.897 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
because they no longer have to
compete with
higher oil field salaries.

30:31.930 --> 30:35.434 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But on the downside, the oil
bust has sent
tax revenue tumbling.

30:35.467 --> 30:40.405 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHAWN KESSEL, Dickinson City
Administrator:
We have lost about $1.5 million
into our general

30:40.439 --> 30:41.406 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
fund.

30:41.440 --> 30:43.608 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's a big hit to the general
fund.

30:43.642 --> 30:46.578 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Our general fund is about $16
million.

30:46.611 --> 30:51.783 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So to lose 1.5 out of that fund
causes you
to be creative.

30:51.817 --> 30:53.552 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
EMILY GUERIN: Creative.

30:53.585 --> 30:57.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If I have learned anything
covering the oil
field, it's that oil booms and
busts force

30:57.756 --> 31:02.127 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
communities, individuals and
businesses to
be creative.

31:02.160 --> 31:04.629 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Take this Taco Bell right on
Highway 22.

31:04.663 --> 31:06.098 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: Take your order when
you're ready.

31:06.131 --> 31:07.099 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
EMILY GUERIN: Hi.

31:07.132 --> 31:09.234 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Can I get an order of nachos,
please?

31:09.267 --> 31:14.706 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They couldn't hire or retain
workers during
the boom because it was so easy
to get a higher-paying

31:14.740 --> 31:15.707 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
job.

31:15.741 --> 31:17.709 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So they decided to triage.

31:17.743 --> 31:20.512 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
For a while, only their
drive-through was
open.

31:20.545 --> 31:22.614 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You couldn't go inside.

31:22.647 --> 31:26.585 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Now they're fully staffed again.

31:26.618 --> 31:31.423 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As we headed out of town, we
drove past the
drilling rig graveyard one last
time.

31:31.456 --> 31:36.695 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For Kessel, those idled rigs are
actually
a sign that the oil industry
hasn't given

31:36.728 --> 31:38.563 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
up on North Dakota.

31:38.597 --> 31:42.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHAWN KESSEL: What that means
is, when they
stack them like that, they can
respond quickly

31:42.434 --> 31:44.269 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
when things change.

31:44.302 --> 31:47.973 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When that price goes up, they
can just simply
move it from that rig yard to
wherever that

31:48.006 --> 31:51.676 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
their is on the wells that they
want to invest
in next.

31:51.710 --> 31:56.581 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EMILY GUERIN: Like many people
in Western
North Dakota, Kessel wants the
oil activity

31:56.615 --> 32:01.953 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to come back, just not quite as
crazy as last
time.

32:01.987 --> 32:12.964 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Emily Guerin,
reporting from Highway 22 in
Dickinson, North

32:12.998 --> 32:14.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Dakota.

32:14.966 --> 32:23.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Tonight, police
officers across
the country are heading out in
their neighborhoods

32:23.408 --> 32:27.646 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to talk to citizens, part of an
effort called
National Night Out.

32:27.679 --> 32:33.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This summer has been marked in
places by shootings
and heated tensions between law
enforcement

32:33.185 --> 32:34.686 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and those they serve.

32:34.719 --> 32:37.756 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But there are cities leading the
way to improve
things.

32:37.789 --> 32:43.395 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As part of our Race Matters
conversation focusing
on solutions, special
correspondent Charlayne

32:43.428 --> 32:46.331 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Hunter-Gault reports from Gary,
Indiana.

32:46.364 --> 32:51.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: Karen
Marie Freeman-Wilson
became native of her native
Gary, Indiana,

32:51.803 --> 32:53.705 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
after three attempts.

32:53.738 --> 32:58.276 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
High on her list of priorities
was improving
relations between the police and
the predominantly

32:58.310 --> 33:03.381 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
black community, not great in a
town with
high unemployment dating back to
the steel

33:03.415 --> 33:09.487 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
mill closures in the '70s, in
addition to
a history of police brutality
and crime.

33:09.521 --> 33:14.659 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Mayor Freeman-Wilson is
starting to change
Gary, and we sat down with the
mayor to discuss

33:14.693 --> 33:16.228 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
her solutions.

33:16.261 --> 33:18.363 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mayor Freeman-Wilson, thank you
for joining
us.

33:18.396 --> 33:22.868 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
How high on your list of
priorities was police-community
relations?

33:22.901 --> 33:26.137 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAREN MARIE FREEMAN-WILSON,
Mayor of Gary,
Indiana: Well police-community
relations was

33:26.171 --> 33:31.877 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
very high on my list, because
public safety
was one of the greatest concerns
in our community.

33:31.910 --> 33:33.578 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: Why?

33:33.612 --> 33:38.149 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAREN MARIE FREEMAN-WILSON: We
had a very
high and still have a high
murder rate.

33:38.183 --> 33:43.221 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We had and have a high rate of
crime, even
though it's gone down.

33:43.255 --> 33:49.828 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A lot has to do with the fact
that there's
frustration associated with not
having employment,

33:49.861 --> 33:53.498 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
with not having adequate income,
with poverty.

33:53.531 --> 34:00.472 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And as a result of that, people
tend to be
angry or angrier.

34:00.505 --> 34:05.911 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And as a result of that anger,
you will find
that people resort to violence
sometimes.

34:05.944 --> 34:10.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: But at
the time that
you took office, there was real
conflict between

34:10.248 --> 34:11.683 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the community and the police.

34:11.716 --> 34:13.985 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What was the biggest problem
that you had
to deal with there?

34:14.019 --> 34:16.221 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAREN MARIE FREEMAN-WILSON:
Well, there was
distrust of the police.

34:16.254 --> 34:18.056 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: Why?

34:18.089 --> 34:22.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAREN MARIE FREEMAN-WILSON:
Residents often
thought that perhaps the police
were involved

34:22.527 --> 34:29.301 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in illegal activity, or, more
often, didn't
care about what happened in
neighborhoods.

34:29.334 --> 34:35.106 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's a big gulf in between
the fact that
some of our police officers do
not live in

34:35.140 --> 34:41.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the city, and, as a result of
them not living,
that they didn't understand what
was happening

34:41.279 --> 34:42.480 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in the neighborhoods.

34:42.514 --> 34:44.316 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: So, what
did you do?

34:44.349 --> 34:48.453 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAREN MARIE FREEMAN-WILSON:
Well, we became
involved in the national
initiative on building

34:48.486 --> 34:54.359 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
police and community trust, an
initiative
out of the John Jay College of
Criminal Justice,

34:54.392 --> 35:00.298 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as well as other organizations,
Yale University,
the National Institute of
Justice, and other

35:00.332 --> 35:06.972 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
research organizations, that
really look at
ways to build police and
community trust.

35:07.005 --> 35:10.976 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so they come in, they talk
to members
of the community.

35:11.009 --> 35:14.913 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They provide training for the
police department.

35:14.946 --> 35:19.317 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Our police officers have all
gone through
implicit bias training.

35:19.351 --> 35:21.086 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: What's
that?

35:21.119 --> 35:26.691 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAREN MARIE FREEMAN-WILSON:
That's training
to really check your biases, to
ask you to

35:26.725 --> 35:29.260 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
look at the way that you look at
other people.

35:29.294 --> 35:33.198 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, do I look at you and think a
certain thing?

35:33.231 --> 35:36.968 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And how does that impact the way
that I interact
with you?

35:37.002 --> 35:43.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, as a police officer, do I
look at an African-American
male, whether I am an
African-American male

35:43.041 --> 35:48.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or not, and think a certain
thing, and as
a result act a certain way
towards that person?

35:48.813 --> 35:52.017 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: So, what
would you
say is the result of that?

35:52.050 --> 35:57.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAREN MARIE FREEMAN-WILSON: What
we have found
is that police listen to the
community more,

35:57.756 --> 36:01.926 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the community listens to our
police officers
more.

36:01.960 --> 36:04.195 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
There's more positive
interaction.

36:04.229 --> 36:10.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have also found that there's
more of an
effort to interact when it's not
-- when a

36:11.002 --> 36:12.971 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
crisis is not occurring.

36:13.004 --> 36:20.779 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so, in August, we will have
our National
Night Out, when the community
comes out on

36:20.812 --> 36:22.547 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
an evening.

36:22.580 --> 36:27.218 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the police, fire, and other
departments
of the city get together.

36:27.252 --> 36:33.491 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it's really focused on
public safety and
the fact that you can go out
after dark, you

36:33.525 --> 36:37.595 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
can interact after dark in a
positive way.

36:37.629 --> 36:40.498 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The police bring their canine
units out.

36:40.532 --> 36:44.102 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And young people will get a
chance to interact
with the canine.

36:44.135 --> 36:45.603 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: And not
be bitten
by them.

36:45.637 --> 36:47.572 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAREN MARIE FREEMAN-WILSON: And
not be bitten
by them.

36:47.605 --> 36:49.207 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's a positive thing.

36:49.240 --> 36:51.643 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: What's
the complexion
of your police department?

36:51.676 --> 36:53.511 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And does that matter?

36:53.545 --> 36:57.348 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAREN MARIE FREEMAN-WILSON:
About 55 percent
of our police department is
African-American.

36:57.382 --> 37:02.087 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Another 35 to 40 percent is
Caucasian.

37:02.120 --> 37:04.722 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And the remaining officers are
Latino.

37:04.756 --> 37:06.691 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And that absolutely does matter.

37:06.724 --> 37:13.264 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think it's important that
young African-American
children see police officers,
see people in

37:13.298 --> 37:15.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
authority that look like them.

37:15.667 --> 37:20.939 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: What you
have achieved
here sounds pretty good.

37:20.972 --> 37:23.575 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It actually sounds very good.

37:23.608 --> 37:27.345 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is it applicable in other
circumstances in
other cities?

37:27.378 --> 37:33.785 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAREN MARIE FREEMAN-WILSON: I
believe that
the solution is really for the
police to establish

37:33.818 --> 37:40.091 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a rapport with the community
that doesn't
necessarily involve an official
interaction.

37:40.125 --> 37:42.627 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Sometimes, it's midnight
basketball.

37:42.660 --> 37:47.298 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Other, times it's some type of
youth league.

37:47.332 --> 37:53.938 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sometimes, it's an explorers
program, where
you are recruiting young people
to be involved

37:53.972 --> 37:55.773 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
with the police.

37:55.807 --> 37:59.677 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Other times, it's just
neighborhood forums
or neighborhood meetings where
you help people

37:59.711 --> 38:01.946 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to keep their community safe.

38:01.980 --> 38:09.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When you know the officers, then
you're less
inclined to think that they are
there to harass

38:09.287 --> 38:10.989 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
you.

38:11.022 --> 38:15.160 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And when you know the community,
you will
understand that the overwhelming
-- overwhelming

38:15.193 --> 38:18.062 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
number of citizens are really
law-abiding
people.

38:18.096 --> 38:21.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: And you
mentioned
earlier the fact that your
murder rate is

38:21.866 --> 38:22.834 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
going down.

38:22.867 --> 38:24.702 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What do you attribute that to?

38:24.736 --> 38:27.472 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAREN MARIE FREEMAN-WILSON: We
attribute the
reduction in the murder rate to
the fact that

38:27.505 --> 38:33.578 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we have now focused on those
most likely to
be involved in criminal
activity.

38:33.611 --> 38:37.182 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so there was a time when we
were just
doing sweeps.

38:37.215 --> 38:40.752 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think a lot of people call it
broken window
policing.

38:40.785 --> 38:42.086 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: Yes,
city of Gary.

38:42.120 --> 38:45.256 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAREN MARIE FREEMAN-WILSON: And
so everybody
would get stopped.

38:45.290 --> 38:46.257 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You might get stopped.

38:46.291 --> 38:47.959 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I might get stopped.

38:47.992 --> 38:52.897 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there might be positive
results in terms
of being able to detect a crime,
or there

38:52.931 --> 38:54.599 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
might not.

38:54.632 --> 39:00.538 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now we focus on those who are
most likely
to be involved in criminal
behavior.

39:00.572 --> 39:06.644 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we send them not just a
punitive message,
but we send them a message that
we would like

39:06.678 --> 39:10.281 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to see you become productive,
law-abiding
citizens.

39:10.315 --> 39:17.755 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We want to support you in that
effort, but
if you choose to continue in the
road of crime,

39:17.789 --> 39:22.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
if you continue to be involved
in non-productive
behavior, we will hold you
accountable for

39:22.460 --> 39:23.628 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
that.

39:23.661 --> 39:25.396 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: And when
do you tell
them that?

39:25.430 --> 39:27.498 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAREN MARIE FREEMAN-WILSON:
Well, we focus
on those individuals who are on
probation

39:27.532 --> 39:28.866 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and parole.

39:28.900 --> 39:32.804 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we conduct what they refer
to as call-ins.

39:32.837 --> 39:35.306 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And so these call-ins are
meetings.

39:35.340 --> 39:40.111 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They're meetings that involve
the community,
meetings that involve
individuals on probation

39:40.144 --> 39:41.913 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and parole.

39:41.946 --> 39:48.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And essentially what we tell
them is, we want
to help you, we want to support
you, but we

39:48.920 --> 39:53.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
also want peace and safety in
this community,
and that the killing has to
stop.

39:53.992 --> 39:57.895 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: Well,
Mayor Freeman-Wilson,
thank you for joining us.

39:57.929 --> 40:05.203 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
KAREN MARIE FREEMAN-WILSON:
Thank you.

40:05.236 --> 40:12.043 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: With the Summer
Olympics set to
open in Brazil later this week,
big questions

40:12.076 --> 40:17.382 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
remain about whether Rio de
Janeiro is ready,
and whether it can get
completely ready in

40:17.415 --> 40:18.383 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
time.

40:18.416 --> 40:19.951 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown has our look.

40:19.984 --> 40:23.988 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The governor
recently declared
a state of public calamity.

40:24.022 --> 40:28.459 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
City waterways are fouled and
filled with
bacteria, streets are clogged
with traffic,

40:28.493 --> 40:31.029 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and transportation projects
aren't finished.

40:31.062 --> 40:36.334 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And beyond the Olympics,
political chaos,
as President Dilma Rousseff
awaits an impeachment

40:36.367 --> 40:38.136 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
trial.

40:38.169 --> 40:41.172 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Days before the start of the
Olympic Games,
we look at the state of play in
Brazil with

40:41.205 --> 40:48.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NPR's Rio de Janeiro-based Lulu
Garcia-Navarro,
Alex Cuadros, author of the book
"Brazillionaires,"

40:48.746 --> 40:53.651 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a look at wealth and inequality
in Brazil
in the decade leading up to the
Olympics,

40:53.685 --> 40:58.823 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and Paulo Sotero, director of
the Brazil Institute
at the Woodrow Wilson
International Center

40:58.856 --> 41:01.492 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
for Scholars in Washington, D.C.

41:01.526 --> 41:02.894 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Welcome to all of you.

41:02.927 --> 41:04.796 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Lulu Garcia-Navarro, let me
start with you.

41:04.829 --> 41:08.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How prepared or unprepared is
Brazil for these
Games?

41:08.866 --> 41:14.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And how are people that you're
talking to
feeling about the Games just
before they start?

41:14.138 --> 41:16.808 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LULU GARCIA-NAVARRO, National
Public Radio:
I mean, I think it's undeniable
that it's

41:16.841 --> 41:22.714 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
been very bumpy, just starting
with the athletes
and the Olympic Village.

41:22.747 --> 41:24.615 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Half of them couldn't move in.

41:24.649 --> 41:30.288 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They had to send in an army of
repairmen to
fix basic infrastructure
questions like electricity

41:30.321 --> 41:32.090 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and plumbing.

41:32.123 --> 41:36.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we have seen a lot of other
complaints,
just today in the media village,
some of the

41:36.694 --> 41:39.630 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
reporters complaining about the
lack and quality
of food.

41:39.664 --> 41:41.299 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So it has been very bumpy.

41:41.332 --> 41:46.504 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
If you speak to ordinary
Brazilians, they
are not surprised by the
problems, but they

41:46.537 --> 41:48.239 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
are definitely disappointed.

41:48.272 --> 41:52.944 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And just to stay
with you a
moment, even today, we heard of
reports of

41:52.977 --> 41:58.483 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
huge amounts of traffic, 70-mile
backups there
in Rio.

41:58.516 --> 41:59.984 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Have you experienced some of
that?

42:00.017 --> 42:01.252 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LULU GARCIA-NAVARRO: I have.

42:01.285 --> 42:06.257 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I mean, Rio is always a
challenging city to
move around in.

42:06.290 --> 42:10.862 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's a city with huge mountains
and poor infrastructure.

42:10.895 --> 42:17.402 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Add to that the fact that you
have dedicated
lanes now that are for Olympic
transportation,

42:17.435 --> 42:20.371 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
buses and cars for the IOC
members.

42:20.405 --> 42:24.242 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's meant that just
people who are
moving around the city in
regular vehicles

42:24.275 --> 42:26.944 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
have had to face enormous
amounts of traffic.

42:26.978 --> 42:33.584 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Getting from Copacabana to the
main Olympic
venues, which are about 20 miles
away, took

42:33.618 --> 42:35.386 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
me about two-and-a-half a hours
the other
day.

42:35.420 --> 42:37.188 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, it is a challenge.

42:37.221 --> 42:40.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Alex Cuadros, the
promise was
that these Games, of course,
would benefit

42:40.825 --> 42:46.130 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Brazilians beyond the Olympics,
right, that
they would reach the larger
society.

42:46.164 --> 42:50.635 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In what ways do you see that
happening, and
where is it falling short?

42:50.668 --> 42:56.641 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ALEX CUADROS, Author,
"Brazillionaires": Well,
look, I think that the Olympics
were pitched

42:56.674 --> 43:03.881 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to Brazilians as an excuse to
modernize all
of this woefully lacking
infrastructure in

43:03.915 --> 43:05.683 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Rio.

43:05.716 --> 43:10.154 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And some of the projects that
were built really
will help the population at
large.

43:10.188 --> 43:15.726 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A number of express bus lines
were created
that are going to be a big
benefit to the

43:15.760 --> 43:23.935 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
working-class Brazilians who can
spend two-and-a-half-hours
commuting each way every day.

43:23.968 --> 43:29.373 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Lulu talking about the
traffic, you know,
she brings up a really
interesting point,

43:29.407 --> 43:37.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
which is, why were most of the
Olympic installations
put in this wealthy suburb known
as Barra

43:37.648 --> 43:39.650 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
da Tijuca?

43:39.684 --> 43:45.122 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's an area of the city where
only 300,000
people live, and where people
are generally

43:45.156 --> 43:48.059 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
much wealthier than the rest of
the city.

43:48.092 --> 43:56.501 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, poorer areas of the
city like the
north side remain desperately in
need of public

43:56.534 --> 43:58.302 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
works.

43:58.336 --> 44:02.073 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Paulo Sotero, of
course, the
original idea also -- this goes
back to when

44:02.106 --> 44:07.845 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Brazil got the Olympics in 2009,
I think -- was
a kind of coming out party for
the country

44:07.879 --> 44:14.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on the world stage, right, to
present itself
as a major power and certainly
an economic

44:14.685 --> 44:15.653 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
power?

44:15.686 --> 44:17.555 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Where does that -- how does that
look now?

44:17.588 --> 44:20.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAULO SOTERO, Director, Brazil
Institute,
Wilson Center: Well, it looks
like the government

44:20.491 --> 44:25.963 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
oversold the story, because that
really didn't
come to pass.

44:25.997 --> 44:33.771 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Brazil a few years after that
entered into
its most serious economic crisis
in a century.

44:33.804 --> 44:36.908 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Eleven million people lost their
jobs.

44:36.941 --> 44:41.512 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So the promise of the Olympics
didn't have
a chance.

44:41.546 --> 44:46.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At the same time, we know now
that people
in the government in the state
of Brazil were

44:46.450 --> 44:53.391 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
involved in a criminal
organization, so says
the attorney general of the
country, stealing,

44:53.424 --> 44:58.563 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
assaulting the largest Brazilian
company,
Petrobras, headquartered in Rio.

44:58.596 --> 45:05.636 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, obviously, if we knew then
what we know
now, I believe most Brazilians
would have

45:05.670 --> 45:07.805 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
been against hosting the
Olympics.

45:07.838 --> 45:14.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And now most Brazilians are
disappointed,
and not expecting much from the
Olympics.

45:14.912 --> 45:18.282 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, Lulu, let me
go back to
you in Rio.

45:18.316 --> 45:21.018 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
One major issue, of course, is
security.

45:21.052 --> 45:25.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
With all that's happened in
various cities
around the world over the past
months, how

45:25.656 --> 45:27.024 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
big a threat is it there?

45:27.058 --> 45:28.793 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How seriously is it being taken?

45:28.826 --> 45:32.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LULU GARCIA-NAVARRO: I think
it's now being
taken extremely seriously, but,
again, as

45:32.129 --> 45:36.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with everything here, the
criticism is that
the Brazilian government took
the threat too

45:36.434 --> 45:38.336 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
seriously too late.

45:38.369 --> 45:42.940 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If you look around the streets
of Rio de Janeiro
right now, it's a heavily
militarized city.

45:42.974 --> 45:45.876 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You have over 80,000 security
forces here.

45:45.910 --> 45:48.446 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's twice the number of the
London Games.

45:48.479 --> 45:50.781 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And so you're not lacking for
security.

45:50.815 --> 45:55.820 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But certainly there are serious
questions
about how safe the venues are.

45:55.853 --> 45:59.357 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There were just questions today
about some
of the security measures at some
of the main

45:59.390 --> 46:01.125 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
venues.

46:01.158 --> 46:05.396 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so we still have to see
exactly how the
Brazilian government is going to
deal with

46:05.429 --> 46:07.198 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the very real threat of
terrorism.

46:07.231 --> 46:11.369 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, Alex Cuadros,
when you
look -- you have been looking at
the financial

46:11.402 --> 46:16.107 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
state and the economic state of
the country
for the last decade or so.

46:16.140 --> 46:21.445 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Apart -- sports aside, what
would constitute
success for Brazil at this
point?

46:21.479 --> 46:23.114 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And what are the prospects?

46:23.147 --> 46:29.253 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALEX CUADROS: Well, look, I
think that the
near term for Brazil is not
pretty.

46:29.286 --> 46:34.625 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, it's in the deepest
recession in
possibly a century.

46:34.659 --> 46:36.394 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Millions of jobs have been lost.

46:36.427 --> 46:42.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, at the same time, I think
that Paulo
pointed to this moment when
there was this

46:42.533 --> 46:49.974 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
amazing optimism about Brazil,
and I think
that people exaggerated then in
their euphoria

46:50.007 --> 46:52.309 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
about Brazil's prospects as a
country.

46:52.343 --> 46:58.783 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think that, by the same
token, right
now, people may be exaggerating
in their pessimism.

46:58.816 --> 47:05.823 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, it may be that we're
approaching, if we
haven't reached, the bottom of
the well, and

47:05.856 --> 47:10.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that simply by virtue of the
fact that we
have fallen so much in Brazil,
things are

47:10.528 --> 47:12.296 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
going to start to bounce back.

47:12.329 --> 47:15.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: You mean
expectations are so
low at this point that perhaps
things will

47:15.599 --> 47:17.368 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
look OK?

47:17.401 --> 47:24.809 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALEX CUADROS: Well, look, you
know, the economy
has shrunk by so much that, when
there is

47:24.842 --> 47:31.282 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a rebound, it's going to be
significant, just
because of the base of
comparison.

47:31.315 --> 47:35.553 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And, you know, Brazil is not a
Venezuela.

47:35.586 --> 47:40.424 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're not seeing kleptocracy on
the scale
that we see there.

47:40.458 --> 47:42.193 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
This is a functioning country.

47:42.226 --> 47:44.628 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's a diverse economy.

47:44.662 --> 47:48.532 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think that, at least in
the medium-term,
it's going to bounce back.

47:48.566 --> 47:52.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: It's also true,
Paulo Sotero,
that we have gone into many
other Olympics

47:52.369 --> 47:55.606 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
thinking, oh, they're not ready,
this is going
to be a disaster, they're going
to have all

47:55.639 --> 47:58.709 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
kinds of problems, only to see
some great
success.

47:58.743 --> 48:00.644 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, what do you think the
prospects are here?

48:00.678 --> 48:04.882 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAULO SOTERO: I think prospects
to have a
good Olympics is reasonable now.

48:04.915 --> 48:06.016 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Reasonable?

48:06.050 --> 48:07.885 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PAULO SOTERO: Reasonable.

48:07.918 --> 48:12.323 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Do not underestimate the
capacity of Brazilians
in general and people from Rio
in particular

48:12.356 --> 48:13.858 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to throw a party.

48:13.891 --> 48:18.696 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Cariocas, as we call them,
are famous
for that.

48:18.729 --> 48:22.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They have the Carnival every
year that are
great parties.

48:23.000 --> 48:26.303 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They happen on the clock.

48:26.337 --> 48:28.272 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And they are very
well-organized.

48:28.305 --> 48:34.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I believe also, as the athletes
converge,
you know, their effort, their
merits will

48:34.345 --> 48:40.584 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
take over, and this will be a
story of the
real Olympics, but it will be,
above all,

48:40.618 --> 48:42.787 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a story about the Olympics.

48:42.820 --> 48:47.424 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This is a very positive,
interesting event.

48:47.458 --> 48:53.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
People -- actually, tourists
coming to Rio
will be very warmly welcomed by
people.

48:53.497 --> 48:54.565 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They already are.

48:54.598 --> 48:56.801 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, actually, they should
mingle with the
people.

48:56.834 --> 49:00.671 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They should go up to the hills
and be with
the people.

49:00.704 --> 49:07.378 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Actually, the best summer in
Brazil are up
in the (INAUDIBLE) in the
so-called slums.

49:07.411 --> 49:09.747 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is a very generous and nice
people.

49:09.780 --> 49:13.517 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, don't equate Rio and slums
with crime.

49:13.551 --> 49:19.857 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Yes, there's crime there, but,
as Lulu said,
heavy security for 15 days.

49:19.890 --> 49:21.358 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
So, enjoy Rio.

49:21.392 --> 49:23.160 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Enjoy the Olympics.

49:23.194 --> 49:26.564 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And, Lulu, just
20 seconds
here, just, is your sense that
people really

49:26.597 --> 49:29.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
feel the weight of this, I mean,
that there's
a lot riding on this?

49:29.700 --> 49:33.270 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LULU GARCIA-NAVARRO: I feel that
they do feel
that there is a lot riding on
this, but they're

49:33.304 --> 49:35.973 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
also very much ready for it to
be over.

49:36.006 --> 49:37.775 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There's been a huge buildup.

49:37.808 --> 49:40.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This has been a country that has
been going
through so many different
things, as we have

49:40.177 --> 49:44.181 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
mentioned, economic, political
crises, the
World Cup just two years ago,
and now this.

49:44.215 --> 49:49.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I think Cariocas want this
to be a success,
but I also think that they very
much want

49:49.086 --> 49:51.255 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
these Games to be over soon.

49:51.288 --> 49:53.791 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, in the
meantime,
let them begin, right?

49:53.824 --> 49:58.128 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lulu Garcia-Navarro, Alex
Cuadros, Paulo Sotero,
thank you, all three, very much.

49:58.162 --> 49:59.897 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
PAULO SOTERO: Thank you.

49:59.930 --> 50:04.768 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Finally, PBS will
be airing
three Olympic-themed
documentaries tonight.

50:04.802 --> 50:09.273 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One profiles the story of
Claressa Shields,
who comes from Flint, Michigan.

50:09.306 --> 50:14.945 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She goes by the nickname T-Rex,
and was 17
when she was the first U.S.
woman to ever

50:14.979 --> 50:17.748 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
win boxing gold in 2012.

50:17.781 --> 50:19.850 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She hasn't lost since.

50:19.884 --> 50:24.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tonight's "Independent Lens"
follows her rise,
but also looks at why she's
never gotten the

50:24.121 --> 50:27.491 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
fame or endorsements that often
follow the
gold.

50:27.524 --> 50:29.293 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Here's a look.

50:29.326 --> 50:30.694 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANTHONY BARTKOWSKI, USA Boxing:
I wanted to
pull us together and just talk
about a few

50:30.728 --> 50:34.999 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
things of how we want to help
you and see
if there's other ways.

50:35.032 --> 50:39.169 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I know you're trying to get some
sponsorships
and endorsements, et cetera.

50:39.203 --> 50:42.840 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: We see these other people
getting all
these big endorsements and all
that.

50:42.873 --> 50:46.777 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANTHONY BARTKOWSKI: Claressa was
one of 46
gold medals for the U.S. team.

50:46.810 --> 50:56.387 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JULIE GOLDSTICKER, Did you even
sit down and
look at who from that group has
the huge endorsement

50:56.420 --> 50:58.222 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
deals, it's Gabby Douglas and
her gym (INAUDIBLE)
and Ryan Lochte.

50:58.255 --> 51:05.129 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When you have somebody who was
in homes every
night on prime-time television
on national

51:05.162 --> 51:07.431 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
television, the reality is
people see them.

51:07.464 --> 51:10.467 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, what do we do to address
that situation?

51:10.501 --> 51:14.872 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I want every time you're on TV,
if a potential
sponsor sees you, for them be
drawn to you

51:14.905 --> 51:18.108 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and say, oh, I want to work with
that girl.

51:18.142 --> 51:25.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we would love for you stop
saying that
you like beating people up and
